  "root_text": {
    "an3.48:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3.48 ",
    "an3.48:0.2": "5. Cūḷavagga ",
    "an3.48:0.3": "Pabbatarājasutta ",
    "an3.48:1.1": "“Himavantaṁ, bhikkhave, pabbatarājaṁ nissāya mahāsālā tīhi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an3.48:1.2": "Katamāhi tīhi? ",
    "an3.48:1.3": "Sākhāpattapalāsena vaḍḍhanti, tacapapaṭikāya vaḍḍhanti, pheggusārena vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an3.48:1.4": "Himavantaṁ, bhikkhave, pabbatarājaṁ nissāya mahāsālā imāhi tīhi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhanti. ",
    "an3.48:2.1": "Evamevaṁ kho, bhikkhave, saddhaṁ kulapatiṁ nissāya anto jano tīhi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhati. ",
    "an3.48:2.2": "Katamāhi tīhi? ",
    "an3.48:2.3": "Saddhāya vaḍḍhati, sīlena vaḍḍhati, paññāya vaḍḍhati. ",
    "an3.48:2.4": "Saddhaṁ, bhikkhave, kulapatiṁ nissāya anto jano imāhi tīhi vaḍḍhīhi vaḍḍhatīti. ",
    "an3.48:3.1": "Yathāpi pabbato selo, ",
    "an3.48:3.2": "araññasmiṁ brahāvane; ",
    "an3.48:3.3": "Taṁ rukkhā upanissāya, ",
    "an3.48:3.4": "vaḍḍhante te vanappatī. ",
    "an3.48:4.1": "Tatheva sīlasampannaṁ, ",
    "an3.48:4.2": "saddhaṁ kulapatiṁ idha; ",
    "an3.48:4.3": "Upanissāya vaḍḍhanti, ",
    "an3.48:4.4": "puttadārā ca bandhavā; ",
    "an3.48:4.5": "Amaccā ñātisaṅghā ca, ",
    "an3.48:4.6": "ye cassa anujīvino. ",
    "an3.48:5.1": "Tyāssa sīlavato sīlaṁ, ",
    "an3.48:5.2": "cāgaṁ sucaritāni ca; ",
    "an3.48:5.3": "Passamānānukubbanti, ",
    "an3.48:5.4": "attamatthaṁ vicakkhaṇā. ",
    "an3.48:6.1": "Idha dhammaṁ caritvāna, ",
    "an3.48:6.2": "maggaṁ sugatigāminaṁ; ",
    "an3.48:6.3": "Nandino devalokasmiṁ, ",
    "an3.48:6.4": "modanti kāmakāmino”ti. ",
    "an3.48:6.5": "Navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.48:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3.48 ",
    "an3.48:0.2": "5. The Lesser Chapter ",
    "an3.48:0.3": "The King of Mountains ",
    "an3.48:1.1": "“Mendicants, great sal trees grow in three ways supported by the Himalayas, the king of mountains. ",
    "an3.48:1.2": "What three? ",
    "an3.48:1.3": "The branches, leaves, and foliage; the bark and shoots; and the softwood and heartwood. ",
    "an3.48:1.4": "Great sal trees grow in these three ways supported by the Himalayas, the king of mountains. ",
    "an3.48:2.1": "In the same way, a family grows in three ways supported by a family head with faith. ",
    "an3.48:2.2": "What three? ",
    "an3.48:2.3": "Faith, ethics, and wisdom. ",
    "an3.48:2.4": "A family grows in these three ways supported by a family head with faith. ",
    "an3.48:3.1": "Supported by the rocky mountain ",
    "an3.48:3.2": "in the wilds, the formidable forest, ",
    "an3.48:3.3": "the tree grows ",
    "an3.48:3.4": "to become lord of the forest. ",
    "an3.48:4.1": "So too, when the family head ",
    "an3.48:4.2": "is ethical and faithful, ",
    "an3.48:4.3": "supported by them, they grow: ",
    "an3.48:4.4": "children, partners, and kin, ",
    "an3.48:4.5": "colleagues, relatives, ",
    "an3.48:4.6": "and those dependent for their livelihood. ",
    "an3.48:5.1": "Seeing the ethical conduct of the virtuous, ",
    "an3.48:5.2": "the generosity and good deeds, ",
    "an3.48:5.3": "those who see clearly ",
    "an3.48:5.4": "do likewise. ",
    "an3.48:6.1": "Having practiced the teaching here, ",
    "an3.48:6.2": "the path that goes to a good place, ",
    "an3.48:6.3": "they delight in the heavenly realm, ",
    "an3.48:6.4": "enjoying all the pleasures they desire.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an3.48:5.4": "attamatthaṁ → ye bhavanti (bj, sya-all, km, pts1ed) "
  },
